## Cache Observability
`GET /api/v1/cache/stats` now returns:
- `hit_miss_metrics` — per-type hit rate, avg latency, error count (in-process, resets on restart)
- `redis_keyspace_hit_rate` — Redis-level hit rate since last restart
- `redis_evicted_keys` — non-zero means memory pressure; check Redis memory sizing
- `cache_version` — current schema version
- `fallback_rate_limiter` — `"standby"` when Redis is healthy, `"active"` when Redis is down

